The paper deals with coding theory and information theory, specifically with polar codes, which are a type of error-correcting code. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses complexity and algorithms, which could place it in cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of Reed-Solomon codes suggests a possible connection to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper deals with communication channels, which could place it in cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
